[The same report was received by ProMED-mail from R.A. Chotani, MD, MPH
<Rashid.Chotani@jhuapl.edu>. Under the prevailing circumstances, the
leashing or muzzling of dogs would be a more cost-effective interim method
of protecting both the dog population and the human population in the
absence of adequate supplies of animal and human vaccines. - Mod.CP
